stant from others. The \"chivalry\" ol\nwhl-h King speaks is the rule of th\nstronger, it Is of .he day when woman\nhad no \"rights\" in the law. only favors:\nwhen \"the husband and wife were on\nand that one was the husband;\" when a\nwlf could not own property, her own\nchildren, and could not even get the\nwages from her own work, when she was\nclassed with \"drunkards. Insane, minors\nand Imbeciles. Yes. \"them was the good\nold days of chivalry.\" God preserve us\nfrom such as those.\nGod preserve us. I say again, from\nsuch chivalry. We do not need favors\nas gifts froan superior beings, but w\nwant our right to have a say as citizens\nbefore the law-making bodies and have,\na share In framing the laws, all of which\naffect our homes, our families and our\nselves. A VIRGINIA WOMAN.\nMorning Smiles.\nPoor Women,\nHe \"A pot is born, not made She\n\"That's right. Blame it on the woman.\"\n-Life.\n3-olved.\n\"Do jou find that the cost of living\nKeeps on increasing\" \"No. 1 have at\nlast succeeded In getting It so arranged\nthat both of my sons-in-law- can live at\nthe expense of our stockholders Chicago\nHecord-Hcrald.\nHe's a Bear.\nAudry Richardson, while visiting hit\nsweetheart in Fredonia lat Sunday\nstrained his arm severely and won't b\nable to use it for ten dais-Altoona (P 1\nTribune.\nTbowaiitleH.\n\"Men are Inconsiderate things.\" oh\nerv-s the bride of a few months.\n\"You are not growing pessimistic al\nready'\" smiles her friend.\n\"Well, they are selfish Yeterdaj\nHarry had th cook broil for him the\nnice Iamb chops I had ordend for my\ndog.\" \"Judge\nrrnntpt Iteaponae.\n\"Mow, mj friends.\" said the candidate\nrraking another effort to arouse en\nthii\"iasm In his hearers, \"what do w\nneed in o'der to carrj this constiti.cni\nlt the biggest majority In its historj\nThe response was Immediate and en\nthusiastic \"Another -ani!idate\"' yelled the audi\nence. London Tit-lilts.\nFooled the Bntehfr.\nThe smart vojng housewife: went tc\nmarket one 